                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.73/190: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-02T14:00:00-03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1919, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 6.48 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Embassy’s telegram of October 24, 11 a.m. Tribunal de Contas yesterday
                    unanimously registered Central and South American Telegraph Company’s submarine
                    cable concession from Rio de Janeiro to Santos and any point in Uruguay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
